The paper deals with revenue maximization in mechanism design, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The focus is on a single seller selling two items to a single additive buyer, which involves optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the optimality of mechanisms, which is a topic in economics (cs.EC). The use of submodular functions and symmetry in the analysis suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
